                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270215-9-off45 t18270215-9-crimeloc48"></join>. On the 16th of January I bound some trusses of hay, and put them on the stack again, behind my master's house - I laid behind the stack, and watched at night; I saw the prisoner come and take a truss on his shoulder, and walk out of the yard - I followed, and stopped him about one hundred yards off, and asked what he was going to do with it; he said, "Take it." I have known him two years - there was no road through the yard.</p>
